# Encryption and keys

## Field-level encryption (database)

- Implemented via prisma-field-encryption annotations in app/prisma/schema.prisma
  - Examples: User.email, AccountRegister.name, RegisterEntry.description, Reoccurrence.description, Plaid tokens/ids, walletAddress
  - Hash companions exist for lookup (e.g., plaidAccessTokenHash, walletAddressHash)
- Codegen outputs app/prisma/reencrypt/* with migrate helpers
- Microservice holds its own prisma/reencrypt/* to run re-encrypt operations server-side during key rotation

Runtime keys:
- DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY — active encryption key
- DB_DECRYPTION_KEY_* — additional decryption keys for previous versions (append-only during rotation)

## Rotation strategy

- Staging has an automated nightly CronJob (key-rotation-cronjob.template.yaml) using the microservice keyrotate image
  - Patches ${SECRET_DB} to add a new key
  - Restarts Deployments
  - Calls microservice migrate route to re-encrypt using the active key
- Admin API: admin/microservice-reencrypt-migrate.post.ts exists in app for manual triggers

## Post-restore (local data hygiene)

- docs/post-restore-encryption-plan.md describes a restore-time strategy:
  - Prefer using reencrypt/migrate with both source and local keys if available
  - Fallback: overwrite sensitive values with placeholders (Users, Registers, Entries, Reoccurrences), null Plaid columns
  - Script: scripts/reset-encrypted-users-after-restore.ts is wired from scripts/dump-and-restore.sh

## RSA and JWT keying

- Table Rsa stores DB-managed RSA key pairs; server/services/RsaService.ts for key mgmt
- JWT secret provided via secrets (DINEROS_JWT_SECRET mapped to JWT_SECRET env). rotateUserJwtKey.ts exists to rotate per-user JWT key references

## Integration secrets

- Plaid CLIENT_ID and SECRET as env; server/lib/plaidAccessTokenCrypto.ts uses @47ng/cloak to protect tokens at rest
- Postmark token and webhook secret from env
- OpenAI key from env; all responses logged to OpenAiRequestLog with metadata

## Do and don’t

- Do not log decrypted values or raw secrets
- Never commit .env; hooks and CI enforce this
- When adding encrypted fields: annotate in schema, run prisma generate, ensure reencrypt code updates; update microservice schema if needed
